{"doc":"Get decimal digit range\n\nIf the character is part of a contiguous sequence representing the ten\ndecimal digits in order from 0 to 9, this function returns the first and\nlast characters from this range.\n\nUnicode properties:\n  `Numeric_Type=Decimal`\n  `Numeric_Value` ","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getDecimalRange?","kind":"def","line":618,"name":"Unicode.getDecimalRange?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/3b873385fdbca8b43ee1e3310bf282743091a14d/UnicodeBasic.lean#L618-L640"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.isDecimal\"><span class=\"name\">Unicode</span>.<span class=\"name\">isDecimal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">char</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Char\">Char</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Check if character represents a decimal digit\n\nFor this property, a character must be part of a contiguous sequence\nrepresenting the ten decimal digits in order from 0 to 9.\n\nUnicode property: `Numeric_Type=Decimal` ","docLink":"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.isDecimal","kind":"def","line":602,"name":"Unicode.isDecimal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/fgdorais/lean4-unicode-basic/blob/3b873385fdbca8b43ee1e3310bf282743091a14d/UnicodeBasic.lean#L602-L616"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./UnicodeBasic.html#Unicode.getDigit?\"><span class=\"name\">Unicode</span>.<span class=\"name\">getDigit?</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">char</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Char\">Char</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><